  "text": "In this work, we will focus on a notion of discrete space. The reason is that many applications, like bike sharing systems or metapopulation epidemic models [CITATION_1] , are naturally framed in a discrete spatial structure. Moreover, in many circumstances continuous space is abstracted as a grid or as a mesh. This is the case, for instance, in many numerical methods to simulate the spatio-temporal dynamics of Partial Differential Equations (PDE). Hence, this class of models is naturally dealt with by checking properties on such a discretisation.",
